  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "AI Researcher (Image Restoration & Enhancement)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Technical direction: Image Restoration & Enhancement</strong><br /></p><p>Leveraging Sony’s world-leading sensor technology, Pentas Vision is committed to driving the deep integration of AI and sensor capabilities. We are seeking a highly skilled AI Researcher to lead cutting-edge research and applications in image restoration and enhancement, transforming academic innovations into real-world products. </p><p><br /><strong>What you will be doing: </strong></p><ul><li><p>Research and develop state-of-the-art image processing algorithms, including but not limited to multi-frame fusion, denoising, deblurring, low-light enhancement, super-resolution, and HDR. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Develop, optimize, and deploy image quality algorithms to enhance imaging performance based on sensor data. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Design and implement algorithmic solutions using multimodal sensor data, and conduct proof-of-concept (PoC) development and validation. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Collaborate with cross-functional teams to drive the successful integration of algorithms into products and services.  </p></li></ul><p><br /><strong>What you should have:  </strong></p><ul><li><p>Master’s or Ph.D. degree in Computer Science, Electrical Engineering, or related field, with a focus on AI, computer vision, or image processing. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Strong knowledge of image processing and computer vision, with expertise in designing computationally efficient algorithms for mobile platforms. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Familiarity with deep learning architectures, with research experience in GAN or diffusion-based image generation, and hands-on experience in model training and optimization. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Proficiency in Python and C/C++, with strong experience using deep learning frameworks such as PyTorch or TensorFlow. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Excellent problem-solving skills, with strong curiosity, self-motivation, and a passion for tackling challenging research problems. </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Strong teamwork and communication skills.  </p></li></ul><p><br /><strong>Preferred Qualifications: </strong></p><ul><li><p>Demonstrated impactful publications in top-tier AI conferences (e.g., CVPR, ECCV, ICCV, NeurIPS, ICLR, SIGGRAPH, SIGGRAPH Asia) and leading journals (e.g., TPAMI, JMLR).   </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Proven track record of success in international academic competitions, including notable wins or awards.   </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Industry experience in relevant fields (especially in AI, machine learning, or computer vision-related projects) is plus.  </p></li></ul>",
